Class Function

java.lang.Object
Function
public class Function extends Object
The Function class holds a method that calculates the answer to a mathematical function using x and y values and a method that saves the x and y values.

      public void logFunction(int startingValue, int finishingValue)

      public void saveFunction(ArrayList<Integer> xValues, ArrayList<Double> yValues)
      The saveFunction method creates an Exporter object and saves the x and y values from the function that was calculated.
      Parameters:
      xValues - The ArrayList of x values from the function
      yValues - The ArrayList of y values calculated using the function and the x values
